 A strong current and low visibility hampered the search, and divers were pulled out of the water Thursday afternoon so it could be lowered. 
 The official death count from Wednesday evening's collapse stood at four, but police said more bodies were in the water. 
 As many as 50 vehicles plummeted more than 60 feet into the Mississippi River, some falling on top of another. 
 The eight-lane Interstate 35W bridge, a major Minneapolis artery, was in the midst of repairs when it buckled during the evening rush hour. 
 First lady Laura Bush will visit Minneapolis on Friday to console victims of the disaster.